dc_description_s: United States. Army Map Service. North Decimal Degree 41.0000. South Decimal Degree 40.0000. East Decimal Degree -3.0000. West Decimal Degree -4.0000. Alternate title: Madrid, Spain. Polyconic projection. With Spanish-English glossary. Relief shown by 100 m. contour interval, gradient tint and spot heights. Standard map series designation: A.M.S. M581. "Compiled from Spain, 1:50,000, Instituto Geografico, 1881-1939; Spain 1:200,000, Cuartel General del Generalisimo, sheets 35 and 45, 1935-1939; Spain and Portugal Road Map, 1:400,000, AMS, sheets 45 and 47, Third Edition, 1943; Railways in Spain and Portugal 1:1,500,000, GSGS, 1941, revised and supplemented from Intelligence Reports, 1942 and 1944. Partially revised from aerial photography, 1942 and 1943.".
dc_title_s: Iberian Peninsula 1:250,000: Madrid, sheet 41. Series A.M.S. M581
